# 🚀 Sentinel-Node: Deployment Guide

Follow these steps to deploy the Sentinel-Node Forensic Lab on your local hardware.

## 1. Initial Host Preparation
Before running Docker, ensure your host system (Ubuntu 24.04 recommended) is prepared for forensic monitoring.

### Install Dependencies
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y smartmontools lm-sensors git

sudo modprobe drivetemp
echo "drivetemp" | sudo tee -a /etc/modules

sudo mkdir -p /mnt/data/services/{adguard,vaultwarden,scrutiny,homepage}
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /mnt/data

cp services/vaultwarden/.env.example services/vaultwarden/.env

docker-compose -f docker-compose-master.yml up -d

Verify that all forensic nodes are operational:
Service       Port  Verification Command  
Dashboard     3000  curl -I localhost:3000
DNS Shield    8083  docker logs adguardhome
HDD Health    8084  docker logs scrutiny

---

